(16, 1, '2013-10-30 14:29:28', '2013-10-30 07:29:28', '<a href="http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/img_external.jpg"><img class="alignleft" alt="img_external" src="http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/img_external.jpg" width="236" height="251" /></a>\r\n<h1>The External</h1>\r\nMorphology of the dental implant consists of three different thread designs according to bone density in each level of implant placement depth.\r\n\r\n1. Supra-fine Thread: These threads are located at the cortex bone area. The threads are fine and small in order to distribute the chewing force, increase the bone contact surface, and reduce the concentration of force at the abutment and implant fixture connection area.\r\n\r\n2. Reverse Buttress Thread: These threads are located at the middle of the implant fixture to in crease the retention between the spongy bone and dental implant. It has also good resistance to compressive force.\r\n\r\n3. Condensed Thread: These threads are located at the apical third of dantal implant fixture. The condensed threads are thinnest at the beginning of the thread. The threads are increasing their thicknesses along the thread line, thus they will condense the soft spongy bone at the apical area during the implant insertion into the bone.<a href="http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/img_external.jpg">\r\n</a>\r\n\r\n----------\r\n<h1>The Internal</h1>\r\n<a href="http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/img_internal.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-15 alignright" alt="img_internal" src="http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2013/10/img_internal-223x300.jpg" width="223" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\n<span style="color: #0000ee;"> </span>\r\n\r\nConnection between dental implant fixture and the abutment has unique characteristics as follows:\r\n\r\n1. Switching Platform ; to improve the biologic width and increase the soft tissue attachment preventing angular bone resorption around the neck of the implant fixture.\r\n2. Anti-Leakage &amp; Micro-movement Connector (ALM) ; the ALM has tapered shape to increase the contact surface between the abutment connector and implant fixture thus prevent the micro-gap and micro-movement\r\n\r\n3. Octa-torx Connector ; this unique feature is designed as an eighth smooth curve for connect the implant fixture and abutment. This unique feature help to prevent the micro-movement and increase the torque resistance. It eliminates the problem about the stress concentration at the corner of the conventional hex connector in most implant system.', 'The Feature of The Dental', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '11-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-30 14:29:28', '2013-10-30 07:29:28', '', 11, 'http://localhost/cust-project/pwplus/wp/?p=16', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(220, 1, '2014-10-16 13:17:06', '2014-10-16 06:17:06', '', 'เจาะใจ รากฟันเทียมไทย1', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '%e0%b9%80%e0%b8%88%e0%b8%b2%e0%b8%b0%e0%b9%83%e0%b8%88-%e0%b8%a3%e0%b8%b2%e0%b8%81%e0%b8%9f%e0%b8%b1%e0%b8%99%e0%b9%80%e0%b8%97%e0%b8%b5%e0%b8%a2%e0%b8%a1%e0%b8%b3%e0%b8%97%e0%b8%a21', '', '', '2014-10-16 13:17:06', '2014-10-16 06:17:06', '', 218, 'http://www.pwplus.co.th/wp-content/uploads/2014/10/เจาะใจ-รากฟันเทียมำทย1.jpg', 0, 'attachment', 'image/jpeg', 0),
